	<Language_en_US>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_PENSEE_STOREFRONT_DESC">
			<Text>Storefront</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_CIV5_BUILDINGS_PENSEE_STOREFRONT_TEXT">
			<Text>The display of a regular item shop (or a not so regular one if you're Recette). All good shopkeepers know that the storefront display is the "face" of the shop. They're visible to anyone passing by on the street, and thus shopkeepers strive to put "eye-catching" items there. The kind of items that make a person think, "I want to buy this more than anything!". Whether you put your best treasures on display or not will greatly affect interest in your business.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_PENSEE_STOREFRONT_STRATEGY">
			<Text>The Storefront is the Penseean unique building, replacing the Market. The Storefront provides a small amount of [ICON_GOLD] Gold and [ICON_CULTURE] Culture to the city, as well as a [ICON_GOLD] Gold bonus. Instead of a specialist slot, it contains two slots for Great Works of Art which, when the theming bonus is achieved, provides a [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism boost and an additional [ICON_GOLD] Gold bonus to the city.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_PENSEE_STOREFRONT_HELP">
			<Text>The Storefront is a Penseean Unique Building, replacing the Market. In addition to the standard Market bonuses, the Storefront also provides +1 [ICON_CULTURE] Culture. Instead of a Specialist slot, the Storefront has 2 Great Work slots for Art or Artifacts. If you achieve the theming bonus of two Artifacts from different civilizations other than your own, the bonus [ICON_GOLD] Gold that the Storefront provides is increased from 25% to 50% and the Great Works in the city generate 50% more [ICON_TOURISM] Tourism.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_THEMING_BONUS_PENSEE_STOREFRONT">
			<Text>Storefront of Exotic Treasures</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_PENSEE_STOREFRONT_THEMING_BONUS_HELP">
			<Text>To maximize your bonus, make sure both Great Works are Artifacts from different civilizations other than the city owner.</Text>
		</Row>
	</Language_en_US>
